{
  "texts": [
    "We present ideas for optimizing the DNN execution to avoid DNN switching (adaptation) costs on GPUs and enable highly efficient execution for batched inferences by leveraging dynamic DNNs.",
    "Furthermore, we integrate dynamic DNNs in Jellyfish and conduct preliminary experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of dynamic DNNs in inference serving systems.",
    "Paper structure The rest of the paper is structured as follows: Sect. 2 introduces the background and motivates our work.",
    "Section 3 presents the overall system design.",
    "Section 4 describes the formulation of the collective DNN adaptation problem and our proposed scheduling algorithms."
  ]
}